The paper deals with sketching algorithms for matrix norms, which involves techniques from data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses applications in machine learning (cs.LG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper uses dimensionality reduction techniques, which are often studied in the context of signal processing (cs.SI).
